title: Man jailed for the insider trading of NFTs - in what is believed to be the first case of its kind
description: A man has been jailed for the insider trading of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) - in what prosecutors say is the first case of its kind.

title: Sara Sharif 'fell down stairs and broke her neck', uncle has told police in Pakistan
description: The brother of a man wanted over the death of his 10-year-old daughter told officers Sara Sharif "fell down the stairs and broke her neck", according to police in Pakistan.

title: Swimmers 'knocked around like skittles' during Ironman competition where two men died
description: An experienced triathlete who took part in an Ironman event where two people died says "swimmers were being knocked around like skittles" in bad weather conditions.

title: Former OPEC president charged with bribery offences in the UK
description: A former head of the group that enables the top oil-producing countries to cooperate and influence the global oil market has been charged with bribery offences.

title: Disastrous luxury event Fyre Festival gets reboot as $499 tickets sell out
description: Fyre Festival - the disastrous luxury party that left hundreds stranded in the Bahamas - is getting a second run, with tickets now on sale for $499 (around £391).

title: House where Hitler was born to become police station
description: The house in Austria where Adolf Hitler was born is to be turned into a police station with a human rights training centre attached, the Austrian government has said.

title: Amanda Knox pregnant with second child
description: Amanda Knox, who was convicted and then later acquitted for the 2007 murder of British student Meredith Kercher in Italy, is expecting her second child.

title: Six children and two adults trapped in chairlift dangling 350m above Pakistan canyon
description: An urgent rescue effort is under way to save six children and two men who are trapped in a chairlift dangling 350m (1,150ft) over a canyon in Pakistan.

title: Breakthrough for studying ancient life as DNA extracted from 2,900-year-old palace brick
description: Ancient DNA has been extracted from a 2,900-year-old clay brick, potentially unlocking new ways of studying life from generations gone by.

title: Releasing nuclear waste from Fukushima is safe - but it's destroyed the livelihood of fishermen
description: The row over the release of treated water from the Fukushima nuclear plant has been raging in Asia for months now, and it has become a complex mix of legitimate concern and disinformation.

title: Japan to start releasing treated radioactive water from Fukushima into the sea
description: Japan is set to start releasing huge amounts of treated radioactive water from the wrecked Fukushima nuclear power plant into the sea - despite criticism from China.

title: Former Man City owner returns to his homeland after years in exile - but his future is unclear
description: In the searing heat at Don Mueang Airport, crowds of supporters gathered from the early morning to witness the moment they've waited fifteen years for - the return of their fugitive former prime minister, Thaksin Shinawatra.

title: Wagner leader fighting to 'free Africa' in new video address
description: Wagner Group boss Yevgeny Prigozhin has shared his first video address since his aborted June mutiny.
